  - Creation=Inexhaustibility of the Creator
Commentary: |
  [The six syllables are] Na-mu-a-mi da-buts(u).
Glossary:
  - Name: Oya-sama
    Description: A name od Amida, expressing loving-kindness.
By: Saichi
Format: verse
---
The treasure of the six syllables was given me by Oya-sama;
However much one spends of it, it is never exhausted.
The treasure grows all the more as it is used;
It is the most wondrous treasure.
And I am the recipient of the good thing.
How happy I am with the favor! â€˜Namu-amida-butsu!'
